Interface Jobs

  • All Superinterfaces:
    JobsTypes, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JobsStub

    public interface Jobs
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, JobsTypes
    The Jobs interface provides methods to create Supervisor restore jobs. This interface was added in vSphere API 8.0.3.0.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        java.lang.String create(java.lang.String supervisor,
                        java.lang.String archive)
        Initiate Supervisor restore from a Backup archive. Use Archives interface to get the available Backup archives. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.3.0.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        supervisor - Identifier for the Supervisor. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisor.Supervisor.
        archive - Identifier for the Backup archive to restore from. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisor.backup.Archive.
        Returns:
        The task identifier for the restore job. The task is cancelable. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.task.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        InvalidArgument - if specified Backup archive is not a backup of the Supervisor.
        AlreadyExists - if a restore job is already pending for the Supervisor.
        NotAllowedInCurrentState - if specified Backup archive ArchivesTypes.Info.getUsable() value is set to false.
        NotFound - if the given Supervisor or Backup archive cannot be found.
        Unauthenticated - if the user cannot be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user is missing the Namespaces.Manage privilege on the Supervisor.
        Unsupported - if version of the specified Supervisor does not support restore.

        Initiate Supervisor restore from a Backup archive. Use Archives interface to get the available Backup archives. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.3.0.

        Asynchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported via the specified asyncCallback.

        Invocation Result:
        The task identifier for the restore job. The task is cancelable. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.task.

        Operation Errors:

        InvalidArgument - if specified Backup archive is not a backup of the Supervisor.
        AlreadyExists - if a restore job is already pending for the Supervisor.
        NotAllowedInCurrentState - if specified Backup archive ArchivesTypes.Info.getUsable() value is set to false.
